This repository is a mixed research package. The license below applies only
to materials that the paper authors or repository maintainers have rights to
license, and it does not relicense excluded, provider-governed, public-source,
publisher, coauthor-controlled, or third-party materials.

## Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International

Author-created repository documentation, package metadata, source-decision
notes, package-boundary notes, file manifests, generated data dictionaries,
and rights-cleared derived package metadata are licensed under the Creative
Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0):

https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

This includes modernized sidecar descriptions and exports for the staged
supporting accessibility and network-measure materials only to the extent
controlled by the paper authors or repository maintainers.

## Materials Not Relicensed

This repository license does not apply to:

- The publication PDF under `paper/`, which retains its publication,
  repository, or manuscript terms.
- Raw Twin Cities Travel Behavior Inventory records, 1999 Southeast Florida
  Travel Survey records, household/trip/activity-space microdata, coordinate
  records, respondent-level data, or Metropolitan Travel Survey Archive
  materials. These are not staged in this repository.
- Census TIGER/Line source files, FSUTMSOnline or Florida Department of
  Transportation model-data sources, UMN accessibility source data, CLUSTER or
  Xie street-classification software, or other upstream/public/regional source
  materials.
- The original supporting accessibility ZIP, the legacy network-measures
  workbook, workbook application metadata, or any coauthor-controlled source
  material to the extent rights have not been separately confirmed.
- Drafts, reviewer correspondence, submission materials, cited references,
  vendor file-format structures, and other third-party or externally controlled
  materials.

## Software Boundary

No executable software, scripts, notebooks, model source code, street-network
classification code, regression scripts, or paper-specific runtime code are
staged in this repository. This root license therefore grants no separate
software license.
